.TH "ibmvscsis_post_disconnect" 9 "ibmvscsis_post_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ibmvscsis_post_disconnect \- Schedule the disconnect
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ibmvscsis_post_disconnect
.BI "(struct scsi_info *vscsi "  ","
.BI "uint new_state "  ","
.BI "uint flag_bits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vscsi" 12
Pointer to our adapter structure
.IP "new_state" 12
State to move to after disconnecting
.IP "flag_bits" 12
Flags to turn on in adapter structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If it's already been scheduled, then see if we need to "upgrade"
the new state (if the one passed in is more "severe" than the
previous one).

PRECONDITION:
interrupt lock is held
